---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { SUPPORT_EMAIL } from "../consts";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy | Explain Yourself"
  description="Privacy details for the Explain Yourself app and marketing website."
  path="/privacy"
>
  <section class="py-14 sm:py-20">
    <div class="section-frame max-w-4xl">
      <div class="section-panel rounded-[2rem] p-6 shadow-panel sm:p-10">
        <span class="eyebrow">Privacy</span>
        <h1 class="display-title mt-5 text-4xl font-black sm:text-6xl">Privacy policy</h1>
        <div class="legal-copy mt-8">
          <p>
            Explain Yourself is designed as a simple consumer game experience. No account is required to use the app, and the default expectation is that gameplay data stays on your device.
          </p>
          <h2>What we collect</h2>
          <p>
            This website stores local preferences such as dark mode and cookie consent. The app itself is intended to work without collecting personal profile data, and no account creation is required.
          </p>
          <h2>How your data is used</h2>
          <p>
            Preferences stored by the website are used only to remember your display choices on this device. The app is positioned so that prompts, round state, and local settings remain on-device unless you later add a clearly disclosed feature that changes that behavior.
          </p>
          <h2>Sales and sharing</h2>
          <p>
            We do not sell personal data. We do not market this app as a data brokerage or ad-targeting product.
          </p>
          <h2>Your choices</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>You can clear local website cookies in your browser at any time.</li>
            <li>You can uninstall the app to remove locally stored app data from your device.</li>
            <li>You can contact support if you have questions about future updates or privacy changes.</li>
          </ul>
          <h2>Contact</h2>
          <p>
            For privacy questions, contact <a class="underline" href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}`}>{SUPPORT_EMAIL}</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
